{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"pwd && cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. [Attention Is All You Need](1706.03762_attention_is_all_you_need.pdf)\n   - Authors: Vaswani et al.\n   - Year: 2017\n   - arXiv: 1706.03762\n   - Why relevant: Core mathematical attention mechanism that motivates the hypothesis.\n\n2. [Neural Machine Translation by Jointly Learning to Align and Translate](1409.0473_neural_mt_align_translate.pdf)\n   - Authors: Bahdanau, Cho, Bengio\n   - Year: 2014\n   - arXiv: 1409.0473\n   - Why relevant: Canonical pre-transformer formulation of attention as alignment and weighting.\n\n3. [BERT: Pre-training of Deep Bidirectional Transformers for Language Understanding](1810.04805_bert.pdf)\n   - Authors: Devlin et al.\n   - Year: 2018\n   - arXiv: 1810.04805\n   - Why relevant: Demonstrates transferability of self-attention to broad language tasks.\n\n4. [Language Models are Few-Shot Learners](2005.14165_gpt3.pdf)\n   - Authors: Brown et al.\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2005.14165\n   - Why relevant: Scales attention-based LMs to large generative settings.\n\n5. [An Image is Worth 16x16 Words: Transformers for Image Recognition at Scale](2010.11929_vision_transformer.pdf)\n   - Authors: Dosovitskiy et al.\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2010.11929\n   - Why relevant: Shows attention-centric architecture beyond NLP.\n\n6. [Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models](2006.11239_ddpm.pdf)\n   - Authors: Ho, Jain, Abbeel\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2006.11239\n   - Why relevant: Foundational generative model often combined with attention-equipped backbones.\n\n7. [High-Resolution Image Synthesis with Latent Diffusion Models](2112.10752_latent_diffusion_models.pdf)\n   - Authors: Rombach et al.\n   - Year: 2021\n   - arXiv: 2112.10752\n   - Why relevant: Practical modern generative architecture using cross-attention for conditioning.\n\n8. [FlashAttention: Fast and Memory-Efficient Exact Attention with IO-Awareness](2205.14135_flashattention.pdf)\n   - Authors: Dao et al.\n   - Year: 2022\n   - arXiv: 2205.14135\n   - Why relevant: Enables attention to scale in real systems and products.\n\n9. [Self-Attentive Sequential Recommendation](1808.09781_sasrec.pdf)\n   - Authors: Kang, McAuley\n   - Year: 2018\n   - arXiv: 1808.09781\n   - Why relevant: Maps attention directly to user behavior modeling in Internet recommenders.\n\n10. [BERT4Rec: Sequential Recommendation with Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformer](1904.06690_bert4rec.pdf)\n    - Authors: Sun et al.\n    - Year: 2019\n    - arXiv: 1904.06690\n    - Why relevant: Transformer attention for recommendation in high-attention-competition feeds.\n\n11. [Deep Interest Network for Click-Through Rate Prediction](1706.06978_deep_interest_network_ctr.pdf)\n    - Authors: Zhou et al.\n    - Year: 2017\n    - arXiv: 1706.06978\n    - Why relevant: Explicit attention over user behavior for ad click prediction (attention economy proxy).\n\n## Notes\n- \"'`paper-finder` service was executed first as requested. Returned results were mostly weakly relevant (`relevance=1`) and not consistently open-access PDFs for this topic, so manual curation with open PDFs was used.\n- PDFs were chunked with `python .claude/skills/paper-finder/scripts/pdf_chunker.py ... --pages-per-chunk 3`.\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/.gitignore << '\"'EOF'\n# Exclude all data files (can be large)\n*\n\n# But include documentation and small samples\n\"'!.gitignore\n!README.md\n!**/README.md\n!**/samples/\n!**/samples/**\n!**/download.sh\n!**/download_instructions.txt\nEOF\n\ncat > datasets/README.md << '\"'EOF'\n# Downloaded Datasets\n\nThis directory contains datasets for the research project. Data files are NOT\ncommitted to git due to size. Follow the download instructions below.\n\n## Dataset 1: AG News\n\n### Overview\n- **Source**: HuggingFace \"'`ag_news`\n- **Size**: train 120,000; test 7,600\n- **Format**: HuggingFace Dataset (Arrow)\n- **Task**: News topic classification (text)\n- **Splits**: train, test\n- **License**: See dataset card on HuggingFace\n\n### Download Instructions\n\n**Using HuggingFace (recommended):**\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\ndataset = load_dataset(\"ag_news\")\ndataset.save_to_disk(\"datasets/ag_news\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\ndataset = load_from_disk(\"datasets/ag_news\")\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved at `datasets/ag_news/samples/sample.json` (first 10 training rows).\n\n### Notes\n- Useful for quick transformer/attention ablations and reproducible text baselines.\n\n## Dataset 2: Online News Popularity (UCI)\n\n### Overview\n- **Source**: UCI ML Repository\n- **URL**: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Online+News+Popularity\n- **Size**: 39,644 rows, 61 columns\n- **Format**: CSV\n- **Task**: Predict content popularity/shares (attention proxy in Internet publishing)\n- **Splits**: No official split (user-defined)\n- **License**: See UCI dataset page\n\n### Download Instructions\n\n**Direct download:**\n```bash\ncurl -L --fail -o datasets/online_news_popularity.zip '\"\\\\\n  https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/00332/OnlineNewsPopularity.zip\n\"'```\n\n**Extract (Python):**\n```python\nfrom zipfile import ZipFile\nwith ZipFile(\"datasets/online_news_popularity.zip\", \"r\") as z:\n    z.extractall(\"datasets/online_news_popularity\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv(\n    \"datasets/online_news_popularity/OnlineNewsPopularity/OnlineNewsPopularity.csv\"\n)\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved at `datasets/online_news_popularity/samples/sample.csv` (first 10 rows).\n\n### Notes\n- Strong fit for Internet attention-economy style experiments (predicting/understanding user attention allocation).\nEOF\n\ncat > code/README.md << '\"'EOF'\n# Cloned Repositories\n\n## Repo 1: transformers\n- URL: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers\n- Purpose: Core transformer architectures and pretrained model APIs\n- Location: \"'`code/transformers/`\n- Key files: `src/transformers/`, `examples/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Install with `uv pip install \"transformers[torch]\"`; strong baseline for attention-centric modeling across NLP/CV/audio.\n\n## Repo 2: diffusers\n- URL: https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers\n- Purpose: Diffusion-model pipelines and components for generative AI\n- Location: `code/diffusers/`\n- Key files: `src/diffusers/`, `examples/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Relevant to testing where/when attention is used in generative pipelines (e.g., cross-attention conditioning).\n\n## Repo 3: RecBole\n- URL: https://github.com/RUCAIBox/RecBole\n- Purpose: Unified recommender-system benchmark framework\n- Location: `code/RecBole/`\n- Key files: `run_recbole.py`, `recbole/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Includes sequential recommendation models and ranking metrics (`NDCG`, `HR`, `MRR`) for Internet attention allocation experiments.\n\n## Validation Status\n- Repositories cloned successfully.\n- README and install requirements reviewed.\n- Full training/inference runs were not executed in this phase to avoid long setup time and GPU/runtime coupling.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
