*Format**: HuggingFace Dataset (Arrow)\n- **Task**: News topic classification (text)\n- **Splits**: train, test\n- **License**: See dataset card on HuggingFace\n\n### Download Instructions\n\n**Using HuggingFace (recommended):**\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\ndataset = load_dataset(\"ag_news\")\ndataset.save_to_disk(\"datasets/ag_news\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\ndataset = load_from_disk(\"datasets/ag_news\")\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved at `datasets/ag_news/samples/sample.json` (first 10 training rows).\n\n### Notes\n- Useful for quick transformer/attention ablations and reproducible text baselines.\n\n## Dataset 2: Online News Popularity (UCI)\n\n### Overview\n- **Source**: UCI ML Repository\n- **URL**: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Online+News+Popularity\n- **Size**: 39,644 rows, 61 columns\n- **Format**: CSV\n- **Task**: Predict content popularity/shares (attention proxy in Internet publishing)\n- **Splits**: No official split (user-defined)\n- **License**: See UCI dataset page\n\n### Download Instructions\n\n**Direct download:**\n```bash\ncurl -L --fail -o datasets/online_news_popularity.zip '\"\\\\\n  https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/00332/OnlineNewsPopularity.zip\n\"'```\n\n**Extract (Python):**\n```python\nfrom zipfile import ZipFile\nwith ZipFile(\"datasets/online_news_popularity.zip\", \"r\") as z:\n    z.extractall(\"datasets/online_news_popularity\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv(\n    \"datasets/online_news_popularity/OnlineNewsPopularity/OnlineNewsPopularity.csv\"\n)\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved at `datasets/online_news_popularity/samples/sample.csv` (first 10 rows).\n\n### Notes\n- Strong fit for Internet attention-economy style experiments (predicting/understanding user attention allocation).\nEOF\n\ncat > code/README.md << '\"'EOF'\n# Cloned Repositories\n\n## Repo 1: transformers\n- URL: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers\n- Purpose: Core transformer architectures and pretrained model APIs\n- Location: \"'`code/transformers/`\n- Key files: `src/transformers/`, `examples/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Install with `uv pip install \"transformers[torch]\"`; strong baseline for attention-centric modeling across NLP/CV/audio.\n\n## Repo 2: diffusers\n- URL: https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers\n- Purpose: Diffusion-model pipelines and components for generative AI\n- Location: `code/diffusers/`\n- Key files: `src/diffusers/`, `examples/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Relevant to testing where/when attention is used in generative pipelines (e.g., cross-attention conditioning).\n\n## Repo 3: RecBole\n- URL: https://github.com/RUCAIBox/RecBole\n- Purpose: Unified recommender-system benchmark framework\n- Location: `code/RecBole/`\n- Key files: `run_recbole.py`, `recbole/`, `README.md`\n- Notes: Includes sequential recommendation models and ranking metrics (`NDCG`, `HR`, `MRR`) for Internet attention allocation experiments.\n\n## Validation Status\n- Repositories cloned successfully.\n- README and install requirements reviewed.\n- Full training/inference runs were not executed in this phase to avoid long setup time and GPU/runtime coupling.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"/workspaces/attention-for-ai-bc53-codex\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"pwd && cat > literature_review.md << 'EOF'\n# Literature Review: Attention Beyond Transformers into Generative AI and Internet Systems\n\n## Review Scope\n\n### Research Question\nIs attention best understood as a unifying mechanism across (1) transformer/LLM internals, (2) broader generative AI pipelines, and (3) Internet-scale user-facing systems that optimize scarce human attention?\n\n### Inclusion Criteria\n- Uses explicit attention mechanisms (self-attention, cross-attention, or attention-style weighting)\n- Foundational or widely adopted in generative AI and/or recommendation/CTR\n- Provides empirical evaluation and reproducible methodological details\n- Openly accessible PDF\n\n### Exclusion Criteria\n- Attention only mentioned peripherally\n- No clear experimental evidence\n- Non-technical opinion pieces without method/results\n\n### Time Frame\n- Foundations: 2014-2022\n- Includes canonical older and scaling-era papers needed for context\n\n### Sources\n- paper-finder script (initial pass)\n- arXiv manual retrieval (primary download channel)\n- repository READMEs for implementation grounding\n\n## Search Log\n\n| Date | Query | Source | Results | Notes |\n|------|-------|--------|---------|-------|\n| 2026-03-08 | attention mechanism beyond transformers generative AI internet attention economy | paper-finder | 6 | Mostly relevance=1, weak topical fit |\n| 2026-03-08 | curated canonical IDs (attention, diffusion, recommender) | arXiv PDF links | 11 | Strong relevance and open PDF access |\n\n## Screening Results\n\n| Paper | Title Screen | Abstract Screen | Full-Text | Notes |\n|------|--------------|-----------------|-----------|------|\n| 1706.03762 | Include | Include | Include (deep) | Core self-attention formulation |\n| 1706.06978 | Include | Include | Include (deep) | Internet ad CTR with attention over user behavior |\n| 1808.09781 | Include | Include | Include (deep) | Sequential recommendation via self-attention |\n| Others (8 papers) | Include | Include | Abstract/Methods skim | Foundations and adjacent evidence |\n\n## Key Papers\n\n### 1) Attention Is All You Need (Vaswani et al., 2017)\n- **Key Contribution**: Replaces recurrence/convolution with multi-head self-attention.\n- **Methodology**: Scaled dot-product attention + multi-head attention + positional encodings.\n- **Datasets Used**: WMT 2014 En-De, WMT 2014 En-Fr.\n- **Baselines**: RNN/CNN seq2seq systems.\n- **Metrics**: BLEU, training cost.\n- **Results**: Better quality and significantly improved parallelization.\n- **Code Available**: Yes (many implementations).\n- **Relevance**: Mathematical anchor for the hypothesis.\n\n### 2) Neural MT by Jointly Learning to Align and Translate (Bahdanau et al., 2014)\n- **Key Contribution**: Introduces soft alignment attention for seq2seq.\n- **Methodology**: Encoder-decoder with learned alignment weights.\n- **Datasets**: Machine translation corpora.\n- **Baselines**: Fixed-context seq2seq without attention.\n- **Metrics**: BLEU.\n- **Results**: Improved translation for long sequences.\n- **Relevance**: Early proof of attention as selective information bottleneck.\n\n### 3) BERT (Devlin et al., 2018)\n- **Key Contribution**: Bidirectional transformer pretraining.\n- **Methodology**: Masked LM + NSP over self-attention encoder.\n- **Datasets**: BooksCorpus + Wikipedia pretraining; GLUE/SQuAD/etc. downstream.\n- **Baselines**: Task-specific and prior pretraining models.\n- **Metrics**: GLUE scores, QA F1/EM.\n- **Results**: Large gains across language tasks.\n- **Relevance**: Generality of attention representations.\n\n### 4) GPT-3 (Brown et al., 2020)\n- **Key Contribution**: Few-shot performance via scaling autoregressive transformers.\n- **Methodology**: Very large decoder-only self-attention model.\n- **Datasets**: Large web-scale text mixture.\n- **Baselines**: Prior GPT variants and task-specific systems.\n- **Metrics**: Multi-task benchmark accuracy/perplexity.\n- **Results**: Strong zero/few-shot behavior.\n- **Relevance**: Demonstrates attention scaling as capability driver.\n\n### 5) Vision Transformer (Dosovitskiy et al., 2020)\n- **Key Contribution**: Pure transformer for image recognition.\n- **Methodology**: Patch embedding + transformer encoder.\n- **Datasets**: ImageNet and larger pretraining corpora.\n- **Baselines**: CNN families.\n- **Metrics**: Top-1 accuracy.\n- **Results**: Competitive/SOTA with sufficient data.\n- **Relevance**: Attention centrality beyond text.\n\n### 6) DDPM (Ho et al., 2020)\n- **Key Contribution**: Strong likelihood + sample quality diffusion framework.\n- **Methodology**: Denoising diffusion with iterative reverse process.\n- **Datasets**: Vision benchmarks.\n- **Baselines**: GAN/likelihood models.\n- **Metrics**: FID, likelihood.\n- **Results**: High sample quality and stability.\n- **Relevance**: Core generative pipeline often paired with attention blocks.\n\n### 7) Latent Diffusion Models (Rombach et al., 2021)\n- **Key Contribution**: Moves diffusion to latent space for efficiency; cross-attention conditioning.\n- **Methodology**: Autoencoder latent space + diffusion + cross-attention text conditioning.\n- **Datasets**: Large text-image corpora.\n- **Baselines**: Pixel-space diffusion/generative baselines.\n- **Metrics**: FID and text-image quality metrics.\n- **Results**: Strong quality-efficiency tradeoff.\n- **Relevance**: Direct bridge from attention mathematics to mainstream GenAI products.\n\n### 8) FlashAttention (Dao et al., 2022)\n- **Key Contribution**: IO-aware exact attention kernel.\n- **Methodology**: Tiled attention computation minimizing HBM traffic.\n- **Datasets**: Benchmarked via model training throughput and memory.\n- **Baselines**: Standard attention kernels.\n- **Metrics**: Speed, memory, end-to-end training/runtime.\n- **Results**: Substantial speedup and memory reduction.\n- **Relevance**: Makes attention economically deployable at Internet scale.\n\n### 9) SASRec (Kang & McAuley, 2018)\n- **Key Contribution**: Self-attentive sequential recommendation.\n- **Methodology**: Transformer-style self-attention over interaction history.\n- **Datasets**: Amazon and MovieLens-style sequential recommendation datasets.\n- **Baselines**: Markov chains, RNN-based recommenders, factorization models.\n- **Metrics**: Hit Rate, NDCG.\n- **Results**: Better ranking quality, especially with sparse data.\n- **Relevance**: Concrete link between machine attention and user attention allocation.\n\n### 10) BERT4Rec (Sun et al., 2019)\n- **Key Contribution**: Bidirectional transformer objective for recommendation sequences.\n- **Methodology**: Cloze-style masking over item sequences.\n- **Datasets**: Public sequential recommendation benchmarks.\n- **Baselines**: GRU4Rec/Caser/SASRec-type models.\n- **Metrics**: HR@K, NDCG@K.\n- **Results**: Strong top-K recommendation gains.\n- **Relevance**: Reinforces transformer attention in internet personalization systems.\n\n### 11) Deep Interest Network (Zhou et al., 2017)\n- **Key Contribution**: Local activation unit for ad CTR using attention over user history.\n- **Methodology**: Query-conditioned attention weighting of historical behaviors.\n- **Datasets**: Industrial-scale CTR logs (Alibaba).\n- **Baselines**: Wide&Deep-style and embedding baselines.\n- **Metrics**: AUC, CTR uplift.\n- **Results**: Better CTR prediction and online gains.\n- **Relevance**: Directly models scarce user attention in monetized Internet platforms.\n\n## Common Methodologies\n- Dot-product attention and multi-head composition (Vaswani, BERT, GPT-3, ViT).\n- Query-conditioned selective weighting (Bahdanau, DIN, cross-attention in LDM).\n- Sequence personalization with self-attention (SASRec, BERT4Rec).\n- Systems-level optimization of attention (FlashAttention).\n\n## Standard Baselines\n- Sequence models without explicit self-attention: RNN/LSTM/GRU.\n- CNN or factorization baselines in recommendation.\n- GAN/classic likelihood models in generative imaging.\n\n## Evaluation Metrics\n- NLP/MT: BLEU, perplexity.\n- CV/Generative: FID, reconstruction/quality metrics.\n- Recommendation/Internet ranking: HR@K, NDCG@K, AUC, CTR.\n\n## Datasets in the Literature\n- WMT machine translation corpora.\n- Web-scale text corpora for LLM pretraining.\n- ImageNet and large vision/text-image corpora.\n- Recommendation datasets (MovieLens, Amazon variants) and industrial CTR logs.\n\n## Gaps and Opportunities\n- Few works unify internal model attention and external human attention in one formal framework.\n- Limited benchmark designs directly measuring whether attention weights align with real user attention outcomes.\n- Internet economics dimensions (competition, platform incentives, attention capture externalities) are often outside model-centric evaluations.\n\n## Recommendations for Our Experiment\n- **Recommended datasets**: \"'`ag_news` (clean transformer ablations), `Online News Popularity` (internet attention proxy), and optionally RecBole datasets for sequential recommendation.\n- **Recommended baselines**: Non-attention MLP/RNN baselines vs transformer/self-attention and query-attention models.\n- **Recommended metrics**: Accuracy/F1 for text tasks; RMSE/MAE (if regression framing) and rank/engagement metrics (NDCG, HR, AUC) for attention-economy tasks.\n- **Methodological considerations**: Distinguish explanatory attention from predictive attention; test causal robustness (counterfactual perturbations) rather than relying on saliency alone.\nEOF\n\ncat > resources.md << '\"'EOF'\n## Resources Catalog\n\n### Summary\nThis document catalogs gathered resources for the project on extending attention concepts from transformers to generative AI and Internet systems.\n\n### Papers\nTotal papers downloaded: 11\n\n| Title | Authors | Year | File | Key Info |\n|-------|---------|------|------|----------|\n| Attention Is All You Need | Vaswani et al. | 2017 | papers/1706.03762_attention_is_all_you_need.pdf | Core self-attention formulation |\n| Neural MT by Jointly Learning to Align and Translate | Bahdanau et al. | 2014 | papers/1409.0473_neural_mt_align_translate.pdf | Foundational alignment attention |\n| BERT | Devlin et al. | 2018 | papers/1810.04805_bert.pdf | Bidirectional transformer pretraining |\n| GPT-3 | Brown et al. | 2020 | papers/2005.14165_gpt3.pdf | LLM scaling with attention |\n| Vision Transformer | Dosovitskiy et al. | 2020 | papers/2010.11929_vision_transformer.pdf | Attention for vision |\n| DDPM | Ho et al. | 2020 | papers/2006.11239_ddpm.pdf | Foundational diffusion |\n| Latent Diffusion Models | Rombach et al. | 2021 | papers/2112.10752_latent_diffusion_models.pdf | Cross-attention in text-image generation |\n| FlashAttention | Dao et al. | 2022 | papers/2205.14135_flashattention.pdf | Efficient exact attention |\n| SASRec | Kang and McAuley | 2018 | papers/1808.09781_sasrec.pdf | Self-attentive sequential recommendation |\n| BERT4Rec | Sun et al. | 2019 | papers/1904.06690_bert4rec.pdf | Bidirectional transformer recommendation |\n| Deep Interest Network | Zhou et al. | 2017 | papers/1706.06978_deep_interest_network_ctr.pdf | Attention for ad CTR prediction |\n\nSee \"'`papers/README.md` for details.\n\n### Datasets\nTotal datasets downloaded: 2\n\n| Name | Source | Size | Task | Location | Notes |\n|------|--------|------|------|----------|-------|\n| AG News | HuggingFace | 120k train / 7.6k test | Text classification | datasets/ag_news/ | Transformer baseline experiments |\n| Online News Popularity | UCI | 39,644 rows, 61 cols | Popularity prediction (attention proxy) | datasets/online_news_popularity/ | Internet attention-economy signal |\n\nSee `datasets/README.md` for download and load instructions.\n\n### Code Repositories\nTotal repositories cloned: 3\n\n| Name | URL | Purpose | Location | Notes |\n|------|-----|---------|----------|-------|\n| transformers | https://github.com/huggingface/transformers | Attention-based model definitions and training/inference APIs | code/transformers/ | Broad baseline library |\n| diffusers | https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers | Diffusion pipelines and schedulers | code/diffusers/ | Generative AI experiments |\n| RecBole | https://github.com/RUCAIBox/RecBole | Recommendation benchmark toolkit | code/RecBole/ | Internet ranking/attention metrics |\n\nSee `code/README.md` for notes.\n\n### Resource Gathering Notes\n\n#### Search Strategy\n1. Ran `paper-finder` first (as required) with fast/diligent attempts.\n2. Because returned results were weakly relevant for this specific hypothesis, used curated canonical arXiv retrieval.\n3. Prioritized papers linking: attention math -> generative AI systems -> internet recommendation/CTR behavior.\n\n#### Selection Criteria\n- Open-access PDFs\n- Strong methodological grounding\n- Widely used baselines and metrics\n- Direct relevance to hypothesis claims\n\n#### Challenges Encountered\n- `paper-finder` returned mostly low-relevance items for this query.\n- Missing shell utilities (`wget`, `unzip`) required fallback to `curl` and Python extraction.\n\n#### Gaps and Workarounds\n- Direct peer-reviewed \"attention economy\" economics papers often behind paywalls; workaround was to include recommender/CTR literature that operationalizes user attention behavior.\n\n### Recommendations for Experiment Design\n1. **Primary dataset(s)**: Use `Online News Popularity` as main internet-attention proxy; use `AG News` for controlled transformer-attention ablations.\n2. **Baseline methods**: Compare linear/MLP/RNN baselines against transformer/self-attention and DIN-style attention models.\n3. **Evaluation metrics**: Classification F1/accuracy plus ranking/engagement metrics (`NDCG`, `HR`, `AUC`) and regression error for popularity prediction.\n4. **Code to adapt/reuse**: `transformers` for attention variants, `RecBole` for recommendation evaluation protocols, `diffusers` for generative-attention case studies.\nEOF\n\ncat > .resource_finder_complete << EOF\nResource finding phase completed successfully.\nTimestamp: $(date -Iseconds)\nPapers downloaded: 11\nDatasets downloaded: 2\nRepositories cloned: 3\nEOF\n'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
